---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import site from '../data/site.json';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | SimploSite"
  description="Privacy policy for SimploSite, describing information collected, use, disclosure, and security practices."
  canonicalPath="/privacy-policy/"
>
  <section class="section legal-page">
    <p class="eyebrow">SimploSite · Privacy Policy</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="lead">This policy explains what information SimploSite may collect, how it is used, when it may be shared, and how it is protected.</p>

    <div class="card legal-card">
      <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> July 5, 2026</p>
      <p><strong>Website:</strong> {site.domain}</p>
      <p><strong>Contact:</strong> <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-copy">
      <h2>Information we collect</h2>
      <p>SimploSite may collect information that you choose to send to us, such as your name, company name, email address, phone number, project details, messages, and any other information included in an email or request.</p>
      <p>We may also collect basic website and technical information such as the pages viewed, approximate time of visit, browser type, device type, IP address, and general location inferred from technical data, when such information is made available by hosting, security, analytics, or communication tools.</p>

      <h2>How we use information</h2>
      <p>We use collected information to respond to inquiries, prepare estimates, provide and improve our services, operate and protect the website, communicate with clients or prospects, maintain business records, and comply with legal or administrative obligations.</p>

      <h2>Disclosure of information</h2>
      <p>We do not sell personal information. Information may be disclosed only when reasonably necessary to service providers that help operate the website, email, hosting, payment, security, or business administration tools; to a client or contractor when needed to process a requested service; or when required by law, regulation, court order, or to protect our rights, users, or business.</p>

      <h2>Method of disclosure</h2>
      <p>When information is disclosed to service providers or business tools, it may be transmitted through secure web forms, email, hosting dashboards, payment platforms, cloud services, or other digital systems used to operate the business. We limit disclosure to what is reasonably necessary for the stated purpose.</p>

      <h2>Payments</h2>
      <p>Payments, when offered, may be processed by Stripe or another payment provider. Payment details are handled by the payment provider according to its own policies and security practices. SimploSite does not intentionally store full card numbers on this website.</p>

      <h2>Security practices</h2>
      <p>We use reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational safeguards to protect information, including reputable hosting and payment providers, restricted access to business tools, secure account practices where available, and limiting retained information to what is useful for business and legal purposes.</p>
      <p>No method of internet transmission or digital storage is completely secure. If you believe information has been sent to us in error or you have a privacy-related question, contact us at <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.</p>

      <h2>Retention</h2>
      <p>We retain information for as long as reasonably needed to respond to requests, provide services, maintain records, resolve disputes, meet legal obligations, and operate the business.</p>

      <h2>Your choices</h2>
      <p>You may contact us to request access, correction, or deletion of information we hold about you, subject to legal, contractual, security, and recordkeeping requirements.</p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this policy from time to time. The updated version will be posted on this page with a revised date.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
